KEYBOARD CHART


This chart displays the codes returned by the console_input() function for
the USA0 keymap.  Use the ci test program to find the values returned by keys
using a different keymap.  The key is from the keyboard, broken into four
sections:  alphabetic characters in alphabetical order, digits in numerical
order (for keys above the alphabetic keypad), punctuation in ASCII order, and
control/function/cursor keys in name order.  The five columns from left to
right contain the codes returned when each key is pressed with no qualifier
key, with the SHIFT key, with the ALT key, with the SHIFT and ALT keys, and
with the CTRL key respectively.  Note that with the console device, the
shifted-CTRL key returns the same as the unshifted-CTRL key, and the
Commodore (left-Amiga) and Amiga (right-Amiga) keys are not monitored.

The codes for displayable ASCII characters are shown below in decimal,
hexadecimal, and character formats.  The console_input() function returns the
other keys as flags defined in console/console.h.  Add the CON_ prefix to all
flags listed below.  Many of the control keys are returned as the flag
CON_CONTROL plus the ASCII value of the character (CTRL-A, for example, would
equal CON_CONTROL+'a' = 1000+97 = 1097).  Note that there are some ALT-key
combinations below which produce no input, and CTRL-(hyphen) returns zero.


KEY            REGULAR      SHIFTED      ALT          ALT-SHIFTED  CTRL
-------------  -----------  -----------  -----------  -----------  -----------
A ...........  097 0x61 a   065 0x41 A   230 0xe6 æ   198 0xc6 Æ   CONTROL+'a'
B ...........  098 0x62 b   066 0x42 B   186 0xba º   186 0xba º   CONTROL+'b'
C ...........  099 0x63 c   067 0x43 C   231 0xe7 ç   199 0xc7 Ç   CONTROL+'c'
D ...........  100 0x64 d   068 0x44 D   240 0xf0 ð   208 0xd0 Ð   CONTROL+'d'
E ...........  101 0x65 e   069 0x45 E   169 0xa9 ©   169 0xa9 ©   CONTROL+'e'
F ...........  102 0x66 f   070 0x46 F   no input     no input     CONTROL+'f'
G ...........  103 0x67 g   071 0x47 G   no input     no input     CONTROL+'g'
H ...........  104 0x68 h   072 0x48 H   no input     no input     BACKSPACE
I ...........  105 0x69 i   073 0x49 I   161 0xa1 ¡   166 0xa6 ¦   TAB
J ...........  106 0x6a j   074 0x4a J   no input     no input     CONTROL+'j'
K ...........  107 0x6b k   075 0x4b K   no input     no input     CONTROL+'k'
L ...........  108 0x6c l   076 0x4c L   163 0xa3 £   163 0xa3 £   CONTROL+'l'
M ...........  109 0x6d m   077 0x4d M   184 0xb8 ¸   191 0xbf ¿   RETURN
N ...........  110 0x6e n   087 0x4e N   173 0xad ­   175 0xaf ¯   CONTROL+'n'
O ...........  111 0x6f o   079 0x4f O   248 0xf8 ø   216 0xd8 Ø   CONTROL+'o'
P ...........  112 0x70 p   080 0x50 P   182 0xb6 ¶   182 0xb6 ¶   CONTROL+'p'
Q ...........  113 0x71 q   081 0x51 Q   229 0xe5 å   197 0xc5 Å   CONTROL+'q'
R ...........  114 0x72 r   082 0x52 R   174 0xae ®   174 0xac ®   CONTROL+'r'
S ...........  115 0x73 s   083 0x53 S   223 0xdf ß   167 0xa7 §   CONTROL+'s'
T ...........  116 0x74 t   084 0x54 T   254 0xfe þ   222 0xde Þ   CONTROL+'t'
U ...........  117 0x75 u   085 0x55 U   181 0xb5 µ   181 0xb5 µ   CONTROL+'u'
V ...........  118 0x76 v   086 0x56 V   170 0xaa ª   170 0xaa ª   CONTROL+'v'
W ...........  119 0x77 w   087 0x57 W   176 0xb0 °   176 0xb0 °   CONTROL+'w'
X ...........  120 0x78 x   088 0x58 X   215 0xd7 ×   247 0xf7 ÷   CONTROL+'x'
Y ...........  121 0x79 y   089 0x59 Y   164 0xa4 ¤   165 0xa5 ¥   CONTROL+'y'
Z ...........  122 0x7a z   090 0x5a Z   177 0xb1 ±   172 0xac ¬   CONTROL+'z'

