RIGHT ARROW .  CURSOR_RIGHT SHIFT_RIGHT  CURSOR_RIGHT SHIFT_RIGHT  CURSOR_RIGHT
SPACE .......  032 0x20     032 0x20     160 0xa0     160 0xa0     032 0x20
TAB .........  TAB          SHIFT_TAB    TAB          SHIFT_TAB    TAB
UP ARROW ....  CURSOR_UP    SHIFT_UP     CURSOR_UP    SHIFT_UP     CURSOR_UP


The codes returned by the console device are identical for the Amiga 500,
1000, and 2000 (to access the special keys in the numeric keypad of the 500
and 2000--the +,-,*,/keys--be sure to use keymap USA1).  For all qualifiers,
all other keys on the numeric keypad return the same code as the REGULAR
codes returned by their counterparts above the alpha keypad.


Keyboard Chart  01/13/90
